Overview.Summary: Hashim Thaci, the leader of the Democratic Party of Kosovo, was elected as the new president of Kosovo by the parliament (1,2,16). The election took place in February 2016 and Thaci received 71 votes in favor (1,2,16). He was inaugurated in April 2016, despite protests and tear gas being released by opposition supporters (15). Thaci was previously the Foreign Minister and Prime Minister of Kosovo (8,12). The election took place in the midst of ongoing tensions with Serbia and Montenegro (16). Thaci has been accused of being involved in deals with these countries that are rejected by the opposition (16). Thaci has expressed a desire to strengthen relations with the United States (18). The election of Thaci as president has been met with criticism and accusations of mafia ties (19).
